Because $\triangle ABC$ is an isosceles right triangle, $\angle ABC = 45^\circ$.  Since $\angle ADB = 90^\circ$, we know that $\angle DAB = 45^\circ$, so $\triangle ABD$ is also a 45-45-90 triangle.  Similarly, $\triangle ACD$ is a 45-45-90 triangle.  Therefore, $DB=DC = DA = 6$, so $BC = BD+DC = 12$, and  \[[ABC] = \frac{(AD)(BC)}{2} = \frac{(6)({12})}{2} = \boxed{36}.\] The answer is 36.

